Play Online Video Poker at Casino 1!

  Even if you're not a poker pro, you can still win large sums of money playing online video poker. You see, video poker machines are basically the perfect, fast paced hybrid of advanced video slot games and online poker. Here’s everything you need to know about playing video poker online at Casino 1 Club.

Video Poker Online

Some people think that you need to be a poker expert to play video poker. But that couldn’t be longer from the truth. In fact, video poker is a very good choice for people who like regular video slot games. The flow of the game is very similar, and video poker is a game you can very quickly come to love playing. The poker-element of video poker is extremely easy to understand, so there is no need to be a poker expert. Even if you’ve never played poker before in your life, you can still enjoy video poker and even win huge prizes.

Play Online Video Poker Games

Video poker is based on a very simple to understand concept. In fact, it's almost as simple to understand and play as regular online slot games.  You get five cards, just like in a regular poker game, and the objective of the game is to get as good a hand as possible.  A “good hand” is not very difficult to understand either, because this has directly to do with standard poker rules. In poker, some hands are better than others. And if you have a better hand than your opponent, in poker you win. In video poker, you don’t play against other players; just against the computer. But you don’t really play “against” the computer either, so your objective is just to get good poker hands. The better the hands, the more money you make!

Make Money Playing Video Poker For Real Money!

Let’s take an example. Say you’ve got a pair of kings on your hand, well – that just made you some money. Exactly how much you win depends on how munch you bet on the round, and the particular game you’re playing. A pair of kings typically gives you EUR 1. In case you have two pairs, this sum is doubled. Three of a kind gives you 3 EUR, and so on. The very best hand you can have in video poker is Royal Flush, and it traditionally pays 250! So, you can see that there is a lot to be won. But wait, because there’s more. There’s an easy way you may double, triple, quadruple, or quintuple that win. And the “secret” is playing with more than one coin. Let’s explain.

Video Poker Coins and Bets

You have a few options in video poker betting here at Casino 1 Club. First of all, you need to choose how many lines you wish to play. This means how many games you want to play. You can choose to play one line only, five, ten, twenty-five, fifty, or one hundred. On each of the lines, you play in a given game you need to bet at least one coin. But you may also choose to bet more than one coin, more specifically up to five. The more coins you bet on one line the higher will your win be. But it doesn’t stop here because just like in video slot machines you need to specify how much one coin is worth to you. Let’s have a more focused look at that:

Jacks Or Better: The Video Poker Coin Values

No, you haven't suddenly jumped to playing online casino Blackjack here: there is an extremely popular version of video poker called “Jacks or Better Deluxe” where you can choose from the following coin values: 0.10, 0.50, 1.00, 2.00, or 5.00. And when you’ve decided on which coin value you want to go for, that’s it! You’re ready to go. Let’s say you’re playing one line only (1 game), that you’re playing one coin only, and that you’re using the coin value of 1.00. Well, if you get a pair of Kings, you get the prize of “one” meaning one time whatever coin value you chose, in this case, 1 x 1.00, which is EUR 1. Sounds complicated, it’s not. Let’s take one more example:

Increase The Number of Coins To Win More 

Let’s say that instead of using the coin value 1.00 you’ve decided on 2.00. Well, with a pair of Kings you’ll instantly get the prize of 1 times coin value 2.00, which is EUR 2! See? The actual sum of money you get depends on the coin value you’ve decided to go for. But let’s not forget the number of coins either, because what would happen if you were playing 2 coins with the coin value of 2.00 each? Simple. Your prize number is 1, times two coins equals 2, times coin value 2.00, which equals EUR 4. So, the more coins you play and the higher the coin value is, the more money you win.

Online Video Poker Rounds

A video poker round is simple and straightforward. You decide on the number of lines/games you want to play, you decide on how many coins you want to play per line/game, and you decide on which value you want your coins to be. Then you hit the “deal” button. The game isn’t over here because you now get a chance to hold specific cards and get new cards for the ones you throw away. So, already here you get another go at getting a great hand. In many ways, you could look at video poker as a two-step video slot, with a twist. But in terms of game mechanics and sheer fun-levels, most video slot lovers report that they enjoy video poker just as much.
